  <!-- BUYER'S GUIDE -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Buyer's guide</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">How to choose the right <span class="accent">SEO agency alternative.</span></h2>
      <p>If you're evaluating options beyond this list, here's the decision framework we'd use ourselves.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Start by counting what your agency actually delivers each month</h4>
              <p>Get your last 3 monthly reports. Count articles, GBP posts, backlinks, and strategy deliverables. If it's fewer than 8 articles and one GBP update, you're overpaying significantly.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Prioritize execution over tools if you have no in-house marketing capacity</h4>
              <p>SE Ranking gives you great tools. But if no one on your team has time to use them, they're worthless. Start with an execution-focused platform (theStacc) before adding tools for analysis.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Check whether published content is portable on cancellation</h4>
              <p>With theStacc, every article stays on your site forever if you cancel. Some agencies retain content ownership. Confirm portability before switching.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Run an overlap period before canceling your agency</h4>
              <p>Start your alternative tool while still on your agency contract. Compare results over 60–90 days before making the switch. You want data before making the decision, not after.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Keep a link-building specialist if you're in a competitive niche</h4>
              <p>Content tools don't do link building. If your niche requires authority backlinks to compete (law, finance, insurance), keep a link-building specialist at $400–$800/month alongside your content platform.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

