      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much can I save by replacing my SEO agency?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">The average small business pays $3,000–$5,000/month for an SEO agency. theStacc delivers comparable content output and local SEO automation for $99/month. That's a saving of $34,800–$58,800 per year. Even accounting for what agencies cover that tools don't (link building), most businesses save $2,500–$4,500/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Will my rankings drop if I leave my agency?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Rankings don't belong to your agency — they belong to your domain. If you keep publishing content and maintaining your local SEO signals (which theStacc does automatically), rankings will hold or improve. The risk of dropping comes from stopping all SEO activity, not from switching providers.</div>
