          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Many businesses run theStacc alongside a reduced-scope agency engagement. theStacc handles content volume (30 articles/month) while the agency focuses on technical SEO and link building. This hybrid model cuts agency costs by 60–70% while maintaining specialist oversight.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the minimum I can spend on effective SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">$49–$99/month with theStacc. That covers keyword research, content writing, on-page optimization, Google Business Profile management, review responses, and social publishing. Google Search Console is free. That's a complete SEO operation for under $100/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long until I see results from agency alternatives?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">The same timeline as an agency: 60–90 days for first ranking movement, 6 months for meaningful traffic. The output from theStacc (30 articles/month) is typically higher than most agencies deliver, so the velocity can actually be faster. Local Map Pack results can move in 30–45 days.</div>
